textRun.content: Building the AI-Powered Support & Sales Agent for Recruit41
A conversation with the CTO of Recruit41

Hi, I’m Kiran, your host today! I’m excited to be joined by the CTO of Recruit41, who’s here to talk about a powerful new feature that’s in the works—a smart support and sales agent powered by AI. This document summarizes our conversation and breaks it down for the team that will be building this feature.
Feature Overview: AI Support & Sales Agent
Recruit41 conducts automated AI-based interviews. During these interviews, candidates often face support-related issues. These can happen

Tools are essentially functions that allow agents to:
Fetch AV health metrics (e.g., video/audio signal present)
Get user’s browser and OS info
Detect if transcription errors are happening
Access contextual alerts (e.g., power outage affecting multiple candidates)
Access application logs for a given interview or given user

“Start small, keep things modular. Build agents and tools that are easy to plug into different workflows. Use real-world examples to iterate. And always keep privacy and human oversight in mind. That’s how we’ll get this feature from prototype to production."

This document should give you a clear picture of what to build, how to build it, and the reasoning behind the design decisions. If you need clarification on any specific part, feel free to ask during the next team sync!
